i feel detached and depressed help everything seems to be okay i dont have friends but anyway im busy so i was happy alone then i saw this other fellow who was kinda a loner too find a partner i was suddenly afraid i will never find someone to connect with i just find many people i come across superficial or maybe its just me but seeing that guy in love and share feelings with someone did make me afraid im just feeling down right now the only person aside from family who truly cared about me left and i will never see again she promised to keep in touch but never called for months now how do i get past this state loneliness is normal to get over this you need to love yourself and do things that you love to get over the fear of sharing feelings with someone make sure you have a sense of who you are i used to feel down whenever my friends weren't around but i started to do things that i enjoy and found that i could be happy anyways also go out and make new friends most people aren't superficial you just have to get to know them first hope that helped btw i would recommend the book feeling good by dr burns it helped me a lot Pok__mon Live! Care Bears Blood on the Tracks The Emancipation of Mimi Shaggy dog story Pitaten Humphrey Bogart Past teachings of Prem Rawat Current teachings of Prem Rawat Social rule Characters in the Smurfs One Tree Hill (TV series) Laguna Loire Moral Politics Angel (vampire) Nicomachean Ethics About a Boy Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Kodocha Kender Theory of conduct Honey and Clover Infantilism Dead Like Me Hollyoaks Israel ben Eliezer Loneliness Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Religious Society of Friends Borderline personality disorder Cliff Richard Dualism (philosophy of mind) Atomic Kitten EastEnders Friends K' Phoebe Halliwell Salad Fingers Rich Mullins Sant Thakar Singh Philosophical skepticism George Burns W.I.T.C.H. Bat Lash Piccolo Junior Saga Mary Jane Watson Big Brother (USA TV series) The Human Stain Luke and Laura Spencer Happin